"profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00406/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00406/canvas/1/7605ee79-50fc-4296-919f-eb8b53a7673d","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T15:19:31.105Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In this set of screentests featuring narration by PTA, the director describes the production team’s process of testing various lenses, props, and decorations until a week before shooting (Visual Storytellers, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW7175947 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY2cCWBS05c\"><u>'Phantom Thread' Camera Tests</u></a>”). PTA wanted to desaturate the image to produce a look that was beautiful but not stuffy in the way prestige shows such as <em>The Crown</em> are. Instead, the camera emphasizes the texture of the filmstock used, a nod, perhaps, to the film’s protagonist.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00406/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:17.434210526315752,58.848684210526336,198.17982456140348,127.30263157894737"}}}]}]}]}